3 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Secretary of the Senate.
4 STATE OF MAINE
5 SENATE
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 767, L.D. 1960, “An Act to Exempt Electronic
9 Smoking Devices or Other Tobacco Products Containing Ingestible Hemp from the Tax
10 Imposed on Tobacco Products”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Exempt Tobacco Products Containing Hemp from the Tax Imposed on
13 Tobacco Products'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 2 in the first 2 lines (page 1, lines 4 and 5 in
15 L.D.) by striking out the following: "ingestible consumer products containing"
16 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 2 in the 6th and 7th lines (page 1, lines 9 and
17 10 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "an electronic smoking device or other tobacco
18 product containing ingestible consumer products containing hemp or cannabidiol derived
19 from hemp" and inserting the following: 'a tobacco product containing hemp'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment removes from the bill the exemption from the tax imposed on tobacco
2244 products for an electronic smoking device containing ingestible consumer products
2255 containing hemp or cannabidiol derived from hemp. The amendment provides an
2266 exemption from the tax imposed on tobacco products for a tobacco product containing
2277 hemp.
2288 SPONSORED BY: ___________________________________
2299 (Senator TALBOT ROSS, R.)
3300 COUNTY: Cumberland
